            <title>[HBASE-585] Thrift not forwarding column missing exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-585</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When connecting to thrift, using the mutateRow() or mutateRowTs() functions, if the column specified belongs to a non-existent column family, thrift just hangs, and the caller eventually gets a TException due to socket timeout.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would have expected to get a more hbasey exception along the lines of &quot;Column family &apos;foo&apos; does not exist for table &apos;bar&apos;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Ubuntu 7.10, running Apache 2 + PHP 5.3 to connect to thrift service&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
